==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: 60
<hw>60</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>one more than fifty-nine;
denoting a quantity consisting of sixty items or units; -- representing
the number sixty as an Arabic numeral</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sixty, lx, threescore</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><h1>60 minutes</h1> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hour, hr</syn> <def>a period of time equal to 1/24th
of a day.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn>⟦br⟧
<def>a 1-hour television program broadcast once weekly on the CBS
television network since the 1970's. Its format is that of a "news
magazine" treating typically three topics during each show, plus
occasional commentary.</def> <mark>[Proper name]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Sixty Minutes</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>60th</ent>⟦br⟧
